contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:21.813 --> 01:22.802
[THUD]

01:22.973 --> 01:24.008
MOTORIST:
What...?

01:33.173 --> 01:35.448
- All right, now I'm getting mad.
- We'll find her.

01:35.613 --> 01:37.649
We'll do a lot worse
than just find her.

01:39.293 --> 01:40.692
There!

01:43.213 --> 01:44.646
WESLEY:
Sorry.

01:49.853 --> 01:52.083
- Your jacket...
- A woman just gave it to me.

01:52.653 --> 01:55.531
She said Jasmine wanted me to have it.
Isn't that sweet?

01:55.693 --> 01:57.923
Isn't Jasmine the best?

01:58.093 --> 01:59.811
- Jasmine's the best.
- She's wonderful.

01:59.973 --> 02:01.929
We should split up.
She can't be far.

02:31.333 --> 02:32.652
Magic Bullet

03:18.253 --> 03:21.086
[CHATTERING]

03:33.573 --> 03:36.610
LORNE: I'm sorry. I wish there was
something I could do, really.

03:37.053 --> 03:38.725
Next.

03:40.493 --> 03:43.883
- I'm too late, aren't I, for a room?
- Yeah, afraid so, buckaroo.

03:44.053 --> 03:46.203
Singles, suites, even mouseholes
are booked.

03:46.373 --> 03:48.523
Pilgrims are pitching tents
in the parking lot.

03:48.693 --> 03:52.891
Try saying that three times fast, and
you'll get a sense of the day I'm having.

03:54.053 --> 03:57.648
I'll give you my house if I can stay.
It's nice. There's a pool.

03:57.893 --> 04:00.612
Sorry. It doesn't work that way
around here, partner.

04:00.773 --> 04:03.492
Jasmine doesn't want your things,
and neither do I.

04:05.013 --> 04:07.129
I just want to be near her, you know?

04:07.293 --> 04:09.761
I saw her on the news last night...

04:09.933 --> 04:13.084
...and I want to say thanks
for making me feel...

04:13.253 --> 04:14.606
Preaching to the choir.

04:14.773 --> 04:17.845
I thought Our Lady of the Perpetual
Seabreeze was the real deal...

04:18.012 --> 04:22.052
...till the divine Miss J. Walked right
through that door and into my ass.

04:23.653 --> 04:25.086
Which is where my heart is.

04:25.893 --> 04:27.884
Physiologically.

04:28.053 --> 04:29.452
I could show you an x-ray.

04:29.773 --> 04:32.003
[CROWD GASPS]

04:34.253 --> 04:38.565
Hey, don't be shy, Slim Jim.
Go get some of that gorgeous goodness.

04:40.093 --> 04:43.085
Hello, and thank you all for coming.

04:54.413 --> 04:56.449
[IN MANDARIN]

05:00.013 --> 05:02.243
[SPEAKS IN MANDARIN]

05:03.173 --> 05:04.526
ANGEL:
How do you do that?

05:04.693 --> 05:07.491
Mandarin's not tough when
you've been around a zillion years.

05:07.653 --> 05:11.202
No, how is it that you always know
exactly what each person needs to hear?

05:11.373 --> 05:13.125
Just look into their hearts.

05:16.253 --> 05:19.962
Or sometimes it's right on their face.

05:21.293 --> 05:22.567
<i>- Senor.</i>
MAN: <i>Si?</i>

05:22.773 --> 05:25.526
[IN SPANISH]

05:25.733 --> 05:28.247
<i>Gracias. Muchas gracias.</i>

05:28.653 --> 05:32.487
- I wish I could see what you see.
- You will.

05:32.773 --> 05:34.286
[DOOR OPENS]

05:34.533 --> 05:38.321
JASMINE:
Hello. My love is all around you.

05:41.053 --> 05:43.726
Will you excuse us for a moment?

05:50.053 --> 05:53.204
- This close, and she pulled a Houdini.
- What's a Houdini?

05:53.373 --> 05:54.692
She escaped.

05:54.853 --> 05:58.129
Fred's obviously learned a trick or two
here at Angel Inc.

05:58.293 --> 05:59.612
But we'll catch her.

05:59.773 --> 06:04.483
- I'll find her. Bring back her scalp.
- No. Jasmine wants her alive.

06:04.653 --> 06:08.248
Right. Fred lives until we understand
why she rejected Jasmine's love.

06:08.413 --> 06:11.769
- Why would anybody reject love?
- Because she has a history of doing that.

06:11.933 --> 06:14.288
Whatever the reason is,
we have to find her...

06:14.453 --> 06:17.172
...so Jasmine can straighten her out.

06:27.693 --> 06:29.490
Would you like to come with me?

06:36.973 --> 06:39.567
And you, my friend, will you join us?

06:39.733 --> 06:42.167
Yes. Thank you.

06:42.333 --> 06:44.722
Bless you all for coming.

06:46.853 --> 06:48.889
Think she'll ever pick us?

06:49.053 --> 06:51.408
If we're lucky.

06:52.053 --> 06:54.931
But not before we find Fred.

07:08.493 --> 07:11.769
Um, hi. You probably
don't remember me.

07:11.933 --> 07:15.608
Three days ago. Mass hypnosis.
You wondered if it was possible.

07:17.613 --> 07:19.763
I read those books.

07:19.933 --> 07:22.527
Some whacko theories, by the way.

07:22.733 --> 07:26.521
All of the mass hypnosis theories
seem highly flawed to me.

07:26.693 --> 07:30.163
I'm looking for mind control that
could affect everyone across the board.

07:34.453 --> 07:36.728
I might have a book on that.

07:38.293 --> 07:40.090
FRED:
<i>Astral Projections</i>.

07:41.413 --> 07:43.768
<i>Satan 's Dictionary</i> ?

07:44.813 --> 07:47.566
You must get some pretty
colorful customers in here.

07:49.373 --> 07:53.764
Used to. You're the only customer
I had since last time you were here.

07:53.973 --> 07:55.122
Oh.

07:55.573 --> 07:58.087
No demand for photo books
of serial killer autopsies...

07:58.253 --> 08:00.813
...when you're living
in a utopian wonderland.

08:02.013 --> 08:03.731
You know what I mean?

08:03.893 --> 08:05.611
I hadn't really thought...

08:08.293 --> 08:09.646
Must be hard.

08:11.013 --> 08:12.969
Hard?

08:13.133 --> 08:15.806
Are you kidding? It's great.

08:16.333 --> 08:18.449
Great? Really?

08:18.613 --> 08:23.482
Yeah. Look at me.
I've never been happier.

08:25.253 --> 08:29.405
Sure. I see it now.
You're practically glowy.

08:31.493 --> 08:34.371
I was flicking through the radio
the other night.

08:34.533 --> 08:37.331
There's nothing really good on
since Art Bell retired.

08:37.493 --> 08:39.643
But ended up listening
to this woman talk.

08:40.173 --> 08:41.447
Jasmine.

08:42.173 --> 08:45.449
Yeah. You too, huh?

08:45.613 --> 08:49.003
What a breath of fresh air she is.
I listened for almost an hour.

08:49.653 --> 08:51.723
I'm a new man.

08:51.933 --> 08:55.812
I used to be obsessed with mind control,
read everything I could get my hands on.

08:55.973 --> 08:58.123
And you don't believe in it anymore?

08:58.293 --> 09:00.045
I believe.

09:00.213 --> 09:02.773
I just don't worry about it anymore.

09:03.693 --> 09:07.083
So you don't worry that it's possible
for someone to send out...

09:07.253 --> 09:11.690
...a biological or electronic trigger that
overrides your own sense of ideals...

09:11.853 --> 09:14.128
...and replaces them
with an alternative agenda...

09:14.293 --> 09:17.683
...that reduces you to little more
than a mindless meat-puppet?

09:17.853 --> 09:21.368
Wow. People used to think
that I was paranoid.

09:22.173 --> 09:25.449
I mean, don't get me wrong.
I've still got the implants in my head.

09:25.613 --> 09:30.164
The CIA is still listening in.
It just doesn't bother me anymore.

09:30.333 --> 09:33.245
Instead, I beam Jasmine's love
up to their satellite.

09:33.413 --> 09:35.802
Share the love with those
MK-ULTRA bastards.

09:36.533 --> 09:38.091
That'll teach them.

09:39.333 --> 09:42.245
Hey. Now I get it.

09:43.653 --> 09:47.771
- You do?
- Yeah. I know what you're doing.

09:57.693 --> 10:00.332
You want to fight fire with fire.

10:00.493 --> 10:04.566
Make sure the government and the other
savages learn about Jasmine's love.

10:04.733 --> 10:07.850
Exactly. That's exactly right.

10:08.013 --> 10:11.244
Why should we be
the only shiny, happy people?

10:12.933 --> 10:16.403
We don't need to use the evil tools
of "the man"...

10:16.573 --> 10:19.804
...when we have "the woman."

10:19.973 --> 10:24.922
We need to trust that Jasmine's love will
reach the world just like it reached us.

10:27.053 --> 10:30.204
Oh, happy day.

10:30.933 --> 10:32.764
CONNOR:
She's been down here.

10:32.933 --> 10:35.845
How old were you when you realized
you could track like this?

10:36.013 --> 10:38.652
I don't know, 5, 6.

10:38.813 --> 10:41.964
Didn't exactly celebrate birthdays
in Quor-toth.

10:42.133 --> 10:44.044
Holtz made up a game
so I could practice.

10:44.213 --> 10:46.647
Oh, you mean he'd hide things
for you to find?

10:46.813 --> 10:49.646
Kind of. He'd tie me to a tree
and then run away.

10:49.813 --> 10:51.371
What?

10:51.533 --> 10:55.572
You know, so I'd have to escape
and then find him.

10:55.733 --> 10:59.487
- One time it only took me five days.
- Five days?

10:59.653 --> 11:01.883
He abandoned you and...?

11:02.053 --> 11:03.771
Connor, that's terrible. That's...

11:03.933 --> 11:05.446
Why I'm so good at tracking.

11:05.973 --> 11:07.691
Fred rested here for a while.

11:12.333 --> 11:15.689
CONNOR AND ANGEL:
Jasmine wants us back at the hotel.

11:15.973 --> 11:17.565
JASMINE:
<i>Before the time of man...</i>

11:17.733 --> 11:23.251
<i>... great beings walked the Earth. Untold</i>
<i>power emanated from all quarters.</i>

11:23.413 --> 11:27.008
I sound like the prologue to one
of those movies about magical dwarves.

11:27.173 --> 11:31.166
- Hobbits. And you watch movies?
- I love movies.

11:31.333 --> 11:34.882
Well then, you should know
this is the greatest story ever told.

11:35.053 --> 11:36.247
Sweet.

11:36.413 --> 11:40.565
The site will be ready in a couple days.
Let me know when you want it online.

11:40.733 --> 11:41.722
Soon.

11:41.893 --> 11:44.453
I don't understand why
you don't go into a TV studio...

11:44.613 --> 11:47.605
...say "Scoot over, Regis"
and sweet-talk your love to the world.

11:47.773 --> 11:50.287
It's not time yet.
There's still a lot I have to learn.

11:50.453 --> 11:51.442
[KNOCKING]

11:51.653 --> 11:53.132
Come in.

11:54.613 --> 11:56.843
ANGEL: You called us.
CONNOR: How'd you do that?

11:57.013 --> 11:59.163
- We felt it.
- We're all becoming connected.

11:59.333 --> 12:04.009
All of us. And now that you're all here,
I want to test that connection.

12:04.173 --> 12:07.483
- We're going to find Fred.
- Isn't that what we've been trying to do?

12:07.653 --> 12:10.087
This is different.
No more running around town.

12:10.253 --> 12:11.971
Everybody join hands.

12:17.973 --> 12:20.931
I can't do this alone. Not yet.

12:21.693 --> 12:24.161
I want you all to close your eyes.

12:25.693 --> 12:29.527
Now, picture Fred.

12:29.853 --> 12:32.686
Picture what she looks like.

12:32.853 --> 12:34.571
Her face.

12:35.373 --> 12:37.933
Her big brown eyes.

12:38.573 --> 12:41.565
The way she styles her hair.

12:42.453 --> 12:45.251
The clothes she likes to wear.

12:46.613 --> 12:49.252
The sound of her voice.

12:50.053 --> 12:53.602
What she looks like when she smiles.

12:56.253 --> 12:58.926
Now concentrate.

13:01.173 --> 13:03.846
Where are you, Fred?

13:04.493 --> 13:06.370
I'm looking for you.

13:12.933 --> 13:16.209
FRED: 219.
WOMAN: Sure. Here you go.

13:16.373 --> 13:17.522
Thanks.

13:21.893 --> 13:24.168
I see her.

13:24.533 --> 13:26.125
I see Fred.

13:39.053 --> 13:41.362
[CHATTERING]

14:04.613 --> 14:06.365
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

14:08.373 --> 14:09.692
There's nowhere to run, dear.

14:10.453 --> 14:13.092
My love is all around you.

14:38.893 --> 14:42.249
Fred, don't be afraid.

14:42.773 --> 14:45.526
Don't be afraid, Fred.

14:55.413 --> 14:56.448
Ow!

14:56.693 --> 14:59.571
- Lorne, a chair!
LORNE: What happened?

14:59.933 --> 15:01.685
CONNOR:
Her hand got hot.

15:01.853 --> 15:03.445
- She's badly burned.
- Call a doctor.

15:03.613 --> 15:07.208
No, no. I'll be fine.
I just need to rest.

15:07.373 --> 15:10.285
- We should get you a doctor.
- I'm fine.

15:10.893 --> 15:14.488
I saw Fred,
clear as I'm seeing you.

15:15.173 --> 15:19.371
Obviously, there's some painful kinks
to work out, but it's a start.

15:19.533 --> 15:21.922
- She got away, didn't she?
- Yes.

15:22.733 --> 15:24.212
But don't worry.

15:24.373 --> 15:27.410
Everybody who loves me
now knows what she looks like...

15:27.573 --> 15:30.724
...knows to catch her, knows to call us.

15:30.893 --> 15:33.327
There's no place Fred can hide.

15:33.573 --> 15:36.531
- What do you want us to do?
- You already know.

15:36.693 --> 15:41.209
She's right. There's work to do here.
We have a hotel full of people...

15:41.373 --> 15:42.852
...people who have needs.

15:43.013 --> 15:45.208
Know what they say
about people who need people.

15:45.373 --> 15:47.887
They're the luckiest people
in the world.

15:48.173 --> 15:50.687
You sneaking peeks at my
Streisand collection again?

15:50.853 --> 15:53.890
- Just kind of popped out.
JASMINE: This is what I'm talking about.

15:54.053 --> 15:57.329
Everything is becoming connected,
the same way I saw Fred.

15:57.493 --> 16:01.008
- Are you saying we're becoming psychic?
- No. What I'm saying is...

16:01.173 --> 16:03.084
Hot water just went out
on the third floor.

16:03.253 --> 16:06.450
And there's a plumber in the lobby
who can help us.

16:06.613 --> 16:08.205
That's what I'm saying.

16:08.373 --> 16:11.365
Now, I need to rest.

16:11.533 --> 16:13.171
Focus on healing my hand.

16:16.053 --> 16:19.284
Oh, there are a pair of sisters
in the lobby...

16:19.453 --> 16:21.205
ANGEL: Blonds.
LORNE: The Bailey twins.

16:21.373 --> 16:24.092
GUNN: I'll ask them if they'd like
to come up and visit you.

16:24.413 --> 16:26.881
Exactly what I was thinking.

16:27.053 --> 16:28.805
This is only the beginning.

16:28.973 --> 16:32.443
No one will ever have
to feel Lonely again.

16:46.853 --> 16:48.844
[TIRES SCREECH]

17:01.013 --> 17:03.368
FRED:
Oh, get off! Get off!

17:07.893 --> 17:09.372
I'm vegetarian!

17:10.213 --> 17:11.487
Really?

17:13.133 --> 17:14.406
With those choppers?

17:15.492 --> 17:20.487
Okay, I eat fish, and occasionally vermin.
But that's it, I swear.

17:21.053 --> 17:24.011
- You believe me, don't you?
- You're still breathing, aren't you?

17:24.173 --> 17:27.768
More like hyperventilating.
You scared the cream cheese out of me.

17:37.253 --> 17:39.323
[FRED GROANING]

17:40.373 --> 17:43.046
What are you doing?
Don't do that.

17:43.213 --> 17:45.727
- Come on, get a room.
- Sit down.

17:45.893 --> 17:49.090
Any monkey business,
and I'll chop you down like a cherry tree.

17:58.293 --> 18:01.171
- So are we just gonna sit here like this?
- Maybe.

18:01.413 --> 18:04.644
Can you give me a time frame?
Because I got a bladder the size of...

18:04.813 --> 18:06.405
Shut up!

18:07.093 --> 18:09.846
I'm trying to figure some stuff out.

18:12.893 --> 18:17.091
WESLEY: <i>Consider her armed, dangerous</i>
<i>and quite possibly insane.</i>

18:17.413 --> 18:21.201
Don't let her grace
or gentle beauty fool you.

18:21.373 --> 18:24.968
Winifred Burkle is a monster...

18:25.133 --> 18:28.330
...a siren, hoping to lure you
away from Jasmine...

18:28.493 --> 18:30.723
...and onto the rocks
of heresy and destruction.

18:30.893 --> 18:32.531
Amen to that.

18:33.013 --> 18:34.287
Now...

18:35.973 --> 18:38.567
...Lorne has a few
important announcements...

18:38.853 --> 18:42.812
...and as I understand,
a very special surprise.

18:43.013 --> 18:45.288
[CROWD APPLAUDS]

18:46.573 --> 18:48.962
Blessings and moon pies,
brethren and "sistren."

18:49.133 --> 18:52.011
I'll cut to the chase and start
with the hourly Jasmine report.

18:52.173 --> 18:56.530
Her Royal Yumminess is currently resting
after a particularly exhausting day.

18:56.693 --> 18:59.890
No word yet whether she'll make
a drive-by this evening or not.

19:00.693 --> 19:03.810
Good news for you third floor faithful,
the hot water's back on.

19:03.973 --> 19:08.444
Okay, and now it's time for that
big surprise we've been talking about.

19:08.613 --> 19:12.242
Tonight, we're going to try kicking it
a little different at Fellowship Hall...

19:12.413 --> 19:14.768
...because tonight...

19:15.053 --> 19:17.089
Tonight is open-mike night.

19:18.133 --> 19:20.567
That's right, that's right, love bugs.

19:20.733 --> 19:22.849
So anyone who wants
to share their joy...

19:23.013 --> 19:25.322
...about good Queen Jasmine
is more than welcome.

19:25.493 --> 19:27.370
So who wants to get the ball rolling?

19:27.533 --> 19:30.570
Why I love Jasmine,
by Linford Ditweiler.

19:30.733 --> 19:33.850
I love Jasmine because
she makes food taste good.

19:34.253 --> 19:36.687
[SOBS]

19:37.733 --> 19:40.964
Jasmine rocks! Jasmine rocks!
[CROWD CHANTING, CLAPPING]

19:51.573 --> 19:54.770
[SINGING]

19:59.533 --> 20:02.093
I have 37 cats...

20:02.253 --> 20:06.610
...and I've just changed
all their names to Jasmine.

20:06.813 --> 20:08.804
[SOBS]

20:09.013 --> 20:12.403
[SINGING]

20:17.453 --> 20:19.091
We should do this every night.

20:31.853 --> 20:34.811
Drafty in here, what with
that hole you smashed in the roof.

20:34.973 --> 20:37.123
You mind if I quest for fire?

20:38.213 --> 20:40.010
Forget it.

20:40.773 --> 20:43.685
I'll just freeze to death.
Not like I care anymore.

20:43.853 --> 20:46.413
- On the run like an animal.
- You don't live here?

20:47.173 --> 20:49.607
- Do you live in a dirt hole?
- No.

20:49.773 --> 20:52.207
- Do you want to live in a dirt hole?
- No.

20:52.373 --> 20:54.409
Why do you think
that I live in a dirt hole?

20:54.573 --> 20:58.646
- You're a demon.
- I'm an executive demon, thank you.

20:58.813 --> 21:04.445
I had an office and an assistant and
a beautiful porcelain cup for my tea.

21:04.613 --> 21:09.209
Now I live in a dirt hole because of those
"Jasmaniacs" and their demon jihad.

21:09.533 --> 21:12.969
Wait.
You're here because of Jasmine?

21:13.853 --> 21:16.287
Me too. I'm a fugitive too.

21:16.893 --> 21:22.092
Wow. Amazing. Two beings,
dissimilar as you and me...

21:22.253 --> 21:26.405
...discovering a shared link
against a common foe. The irony.

21:26.573 --> 21:29.246
My feelings for you are changing.

21:29.413 --> 21:31.563
I feel...

21:31.733 --> 21:33.963
...warmth.

21:34.613 --> 21:37.764
Wait. No, I don't.

21:37.933 --> 21:40.572
That's me wetting myself
because you wouldn't let me pee!

21:40.733 --> 21:43.930
- Thanks for nothing.
- Hey, I'm new to this fugitive thing.

21:44.093 --> 21:47.403
I've been trying to suss out all night
how Jasmine controls people.

21:47.573 --> 21:51.043
- We have to stop her.
- Okay, fine, we'll stop her.

21:51.373 --> 21:53.364
But not tonight.

21:54.053 --> 21:57.443
Not till I've had a little shuteye.
I'm beat.

22:02.133 --> 22:06.126
Hey, these yours?
Because I've never seen them before.

22:06.293 --> 22:10.969
Why would anyone keep a stash
of these tasty little...?

22:11.133 --> 22:15.843
I mean, disgusting, meaty things
like this laying around?

22:17.453 --> 22:22.163
Okay, so not a vegetarian.

22:28.573 --> 22:30.165
Finger food?

22:30.493 --> 22:32.768
[GROWLS]
[FRED SCREAMS]

22:35.373 --> 22:38.092
I got your demon jihad right here!

23:26.213 --> 23:28.363
Here I am.

23:28.533 --> 23:30.364
Come and get me.

23:31.573 --> 23:33.291
Fred.

23:38.293 --> 23:39.612
Hey, Fred.

23:40.533 --> 23:43.172
- You know my name.
- You're famous.

23:43.573 --> 23:46.246
I'll chop out your implants,
you come any closer.

23:46.413 --> 23:49.450
No need to worry. We're under
strict orders not to hurt you.

23:51.013 --> 23:53.288
So Jasmine's coming for me?

23:53.933 --> 23:55.207
Yeah.

23:56.373 --> 23:58.523
Hey, could I get your autograph?

24:00.053 --> 24:02.442
Anything for a fan.

24:03.573 --> 24:06.770
- Who should I sign it to?
JASMINE: To me, of course.

24:15.093 --> 24:17.129
And to reward you
for your faithfulness:

24:19.053 --> 24:23.331
Dallas, November 22nd, 1963.

24:23.773 --> 24:25.604
There was no second gunman.

24:25.773 --> 24:27.809
Oswald acted alone.

24:28.373 --> 24:30.284
Oh, my God.

24:36.733 --> 24:39.372
You know that I love you,
don't you, Fred?

24:40.813 --> 24:45.329
And there's nothing you can do or say
to make me stop loving you.

24:48.613 --> 24:50.683
I'm so sorry.

24:50.973 --> 24:52.804
It's okay.

24:53.333 --> 24:55.449
I forgive you.

24:56.573 --> 24:58.325
No.

24:58.493 --> 25:01.007
I'm talking to Angel.

25:01.173 --> 25:03.129
I hope he can forgive me.

25:31.773 --> 25:35.527
Dumb idea for such a smarty.
You know bullets don't kill me.

25:37.053 --> 25:39.521
Wanna see how they work on you?

25:41.813 --> 25:44.008
Look at her.

25:53.013 --> 25:54.685
No.

25:55.493 --> 25:56.767
Angel?

25:58.693 --> 26:00.570
I'm sorry.

26:02.213 --> 26:04.681
I had to show you.

26:04.853 --> 26:07.367
- I'm so sorry.
- Show you what?

26:07.533 --> 26:10.411
No, it can't be. No.

26:11.733 --> 26:15.169
- My blood.
- Dad, what's going on?

26:15.333 --> 26:18.325
Don't. He's been infected.

26:23.613 --> 26:27.572
I'm sorry, Connor.
He's as dead to us as Fred.

26:32.773 --> 26:34.491
I loved you so much.

26:42.013 --> 26:43.492
We need to get you out of here.

26:50.893 --> 26:52.645
You ruin everything.

27:02.133 --> 27:03.930
I don't understand.

27:04.093 --> 27:05.845
How did it happen?

27:06.453 --> 27:07.772
Let them go.

27:07.933 --> 27:09.924
- They have to be stopped.
- I need your help.

27:17.853 --> 27:22.563
- Wow, so much blood.
- Stay away from it, both of you.

27:22.733 --> 27:25.088
- We need to clean this up.
- I'll do it.

27:25.253 --> 27:26.811
No.

27:30.293 --> 27:32.887
- Burn it to the ground.
- Okay.

27:44.133 --> 27:46.169
You want me to stay here?

28:06.013 --> 28:07.844
As scrump-tilly-icious as these are...

28:08.013 --> 28:10.766
...they'd be tastier if our
cocoa-colored queen were here.

28:10.933 --> 28:15.131
I heard that. I keep shoveling pie
into my hole and still feel empty.

28:15.293 --> 28:17.966
Anybody else picking up
on some weird feelings?

28:18.133 --> 28:20.010
Something's definitely off.

28:20.173 --> 28:24.052
But without Jasmine around,
I can't sense it specifically.

28:24.213 --> 28:26.886
- You getting anything?
- A visual on our lovely leader.

28:27.053 --> 28:30.841
A visual? Really? Some gift
you got there, Kreskin. Where is she?

28:31.013 --> 28:32.844
Over yonder.

28:37.973 --> 28:40.407
Shouldn't Angel be with them?

28:51.813 --> 28:54.008
I'll make this brief.

28:55.053 --> 28:58.728
Fred infected Angel.
He's gone. Lost to us.

28:58.893 --> 28:59.882
GUNN:
What?

29:00.533 --> 29:03.923
Don't worry. I'm not
so easily undone as that.

29:05.213 --> 29:08.046
Any idea how she did it,
how Fred turned him?

29:08.213 --> 29:11.091
Yes. My kindness turned him.

29:11.253 --> 29:14.051
By being loving to Fred,
I opened the door to her hate.

29:14.213 --> 29:16.773
By trying to save Fred, I lost Angel.

29:18.693 --> 29:20.649
It won't happen again.

29:20.813 --> 29:24.089
We must eradicate their hate.

29:30.733 --> 29:31.722
You.

29:33.333 --> 29:34.607
You.

29:35.093 --> 29:38.688
And you, come with me. Connor.

29:43.173 --> 29:46.768
I can't believe Fred managed
to sway Angel back to the dark side.

29:46.933 --> 29:50.892
Evil, not evil, evil again.
I wish he'd make up his mind.

29:51.053 --> 29:54.011
I guess the good news is
it doesn't matter anymore.

29:54.173 --> 29:58.689
Jasmine says Angel has to die,
he dies.

30:25.013 --> 30:26.446
Angel?

30:28.613 --> 30:30.729
You okay?

30:31.013 --> 30:33.402
Bullet feels like a bee sting.

30:35.813 --> 30:40.011
- That's not what I meant.
- I know. I don't want to talk about it.

30:43.453 --> 30:45.683
I think you do.

30:47.453 --> 30:49.808
I miss her so much.

30:51.213 --> 30:53.443
I never...

30:55.333 --> 30:57.449
I know.

30:58.773 --> 31:01.731
It's been over a week,
and I still cry.

31:04.733 --> 31:07.372
Part of me wishes
I still believed the lie.

31:07.533 --> 31:10.684
Well, why don't we?
I mean, I'm not exactly clear on...

31:10.853 --> 31:12.844
Jasmine's blood.

31:13.373 --> 31:15.489
It was on the bullet that hit you.

31:17.093 --> 31:20.642
Somehow, it breaks her spell
when it mingles with ours.

31:23.173 --> 31:27.849
It must've got in my system when I was
trying to get the blood off her blouse.

31:30.093 --> 31:32.288
You did the right thing, Fred.

31:32.453 --> 31:34.762
It took a lot of courage.

31:35.013 --> 31:37.402
[CRYING]

31:41.453 --> 31:44.172
ANGEL:
It must've been hard for you.

31:45.293 --> 31:47.488
I'm sorry.

31:49.813 --> 31:52.566
I've been so alone...

31:53.133 --> 31:55.567
...and scared.

31:57.813 --> 32:00.611
I'm not like you...

32:00.773 --> 32:03.287
...not a champion.

32:05.253 --> 32:08.051
Everything I see says different.

32:09.933 --> 32:13.608
We need more of Jasmine's blood.
We have to help the others.

32:13.773 --> 32:17.561
- We'll never get close to her. Not now.
- Then we need another way.

32:20.893 --> 32:21.882
What?

32:23.413 --> 32:26.291
It's pretty horrible, but may...

32:26.453 --> 32:28.967
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

32:36.253 --> 32:38.687
You think they bought it?

32:38.853 --> 32:40.206
I did.

32:40.373 --> 32:43.729
I mean, I didn't hear anything.

32:45.333 --> 32:48.086
WOMAN: Angel.
MAN 1: You're dead, Fred.

32:48.813 --> 32:50.690
I'm thinking they didn't buy it.

32:50.973 --> 32:52.406
MAN 2:
Get them!

33:12.533 --> 33:16.811
Stand guard. No one
comes into the hallway.

33:26.253 --> 33:28.084
Over there.

33:29.693 --> 33:31.251
Take off your clothes.

34:38.813 --> 34:40.451
[CLATTERS]

34:51.973 --> 34:54.726
FRED: I can't even count
all the ways this is wrong.

34:54.893 --> 34:58.727
It's not like she'll feel it, right?
I mean, she's...

34:58.893 --> 35:00.212
Brain dead?

35:00.373 --> 35:03.888
Expression doesn't exactly leave
a lot to the imagination, does it?

35:04.053 --> 35:06.647
Just makes what I have to do
a little easier.

35:23.333 --> 35:24.925
ANGEL WHISPERING:
I'm so sorry.

35:35.813 --> 35:40.443
Oh, my God, she's awake.
Cordy? Cordelia, can you hear me?

35:40.613 --> 35:42.683
We're right here.
She grabbed my hand.

35:42.853 --> 35:46.971
Angel, people in comas,
sometimes their bodies just do things...

35:47.133 --> 35:50.091
...mumble words,
maybe even open their eyes.

35:50.253 --> 35:52.369
It doesn't necessarily mean
they're waking up.

35:52.533 --> 35:54.649
But it could.
Stranger things have happened.

35:54.813 --> 35:58.044
Like Cordelia giving birth
to a beautiful ebony goddess?

36:00.013 --> 36:04.689
Not the example I was looking for,
but yeah.

36:04.893 --> 36:06.611
I know.

36:07.453 --> 36:09.284
Sorry.

36:10.613 --> 36:13.366
Maybe we should get this over with.

36:28.973 --> 36:31.123
Is that enough?

36:32.493 --> 36:34.927
Any more room at the inn?

36:36.773 --> 36:40.732
Look at this. Pigs in paradise.

36:42.493 --> 36:44.688
Mind if I pay my respects
to the woman...

36:44.853 --> 36:47.890
...who made peace on Earth
a possible possibility?

36:50.933 --> 36:53.606
Thank you, Cordelia,
for your sacrifice.

36:53.773 --> 36:56.606
For bringing our Jasmine
into the world and...

37:00.853 --> 37:03.128
Hey, hey, what
are you doing to the...?

37:03.453 --> 37:05.409
[MUFFLED YELLING]

37:18.253 --> 37:21.086
You're the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

37:21.933 --> 37:24.686
My sweet boy.

37:27.053 --> 37:28.725
Where are those people?

37:29.093 --> 37:31.049
I ate them.

37:33.293 --> 37:35.045
Cool.

37:41.173 --> 37:43.641
You're sure you can do this?

37:54.213 --> 37:56.204
Hallelujah.

37:59.813 --> 38:01.804
Hey, I'm praising Jasmine.
How about you?

38:01.973 --> 38:04.123
- Yeah.
- Okay.

38:05.693 --> 38:08.890
Tonight, the role of Judas Iscariot
will be played by Krevlornswath...

38:09.053 --> 38:11.362
...of the Deathwok Clan.

38:13.573 --> 38:16.849
Hey, feeling the love, huh?
Thank you, Jasmine.

38:17.013 --> 38:18.890
Feeling the love.

38:19.053 --> 38:20.930
Hey, good news, my devoted darlings.

38:21.093 --> 38:25.132
Jasmine's pulling you off stacking duty,
wants to see us ASAP for a little TLC.

38:25.293 --> 38:26.772
Really?

38:26.933 --> 38:29.367
- I haven't sensed anything, have you?
- No.

38:29.533 --> 38:31.967
Everything else
has been feeling pretty clear.

38:34.613 --> 38:36.968
What happened to you?

38:38.373 --> 38:40.728
- What do you mean?
- Your wrist. You've cut it.

38:41.013 --> 38:43.288
Oh, it's... That is...

38:43.453 --> 38:46.365
That's a long, boring story. Come on.

39:05.533 --> 39:08.047
[THUDDING AND GRUNTING]

39:16.973 --> 39:18.645
How did you figure it out?

39:19.093 --> 39:20.526
It was Angel.

39:22.293 --> 39:24.523
He figured since Cordy
gave birth to Jasmine...

39:24.693 --> 39:27.571
...they might share a blood link
as well as a mystical one.

39:27.733 --> 39:33.126
We hoped Cordy's blood would have the
same effect when we exposed you to it.

39:33.293 --> 39:35.124
- Thanks for nothing.
LORNE: Yeah.

39:35.293 --> 39:38.729
You slashed this wrist, and
I'm ready to do the other one myself.

39:38.893 --> 39:41.453
Everything we believed...

39:42.613 --> 39:44.012
...deception.

39:44.173 --> 39:48.883
How do we convince several million
people that Jasmine's message is false?

39:49.053 --> 39:50.247
It's impossible.

39:50.413 --> 39:55.282
Even if we're able to develop a synthetic
analog to the blood, there's...

39:55.813 --> 39:58.964
I mean, how do we fight something
this huge and powerful?

39:59.133 --> 40:00.407
I don't know yet.

40:00.573 --> 40:03.849
But what I do know is that I'm not
leaving this hotel without my son.

40:06.973 --> 40:08.292
I'll get him.

40:09.973 --> 40:11.804
I've kidnapped him before.

40:31.453 --> 40:33.205
What?

40:34.533 --> 40:35.648
Hey...

40:35.813 --> 40:37.610
- No!
- It's gonna be okay.

40:38.693 --> 40:42.083
- You've been lied to. We all have.
ANGEL: Don't make this any harder.

40:42.253 --> 40:43.732
Let go!

40:45.933 --> 40:47.252
ANGEL:
Easy!

40:48.053 --> 40:49.406
Don't.

40:53.573 --> 40:55.609
- I'll kill you!
- It'll pass.

40:55.773 --> 40:58.333
Right, because Lord knows
he's never tried that before.

40:58.693 --> 41:00.331
You're back with us now, Connor.

41:08.533 --> 41:10.524
ANGEL:
Sorry.

41:10.773 --> 41:12.889
The only way to make you see.

41:13.533 --> 41:16.286
What you're feeling is normal.

41:16.453 --> 41:18.808
We're all feeling it, the sadness.

41:21.453 --> 41:24.365
It gets better after a while.

41:25.093 --> 41:27.163
Jasmine.

41:27.653 --> 41:29.883
You understand why we're here?

41:41.453 --> 41:43.330
[CLANKS]

41:50.733 --> 41:52.405
They're here!

41:52.893 --> 41:54.884
Come quick! They're here!

